    • ofAll

      public static <E> @Unmodifiable MLImmutableSet<E> ofAll(Collection<E> collection)
      Create an immutable set from a collection of elements. This method is not guaranteed to copy the collection, but is guaranteed to be immutable and unmodifiable, including if the provided collection changes.
      Type Parameters:
      E - the type of the elements in the collection
      Parameters:
      collection - the collection to create the set from
      Returns:
      a new immutable set containing the elements of the collection

    • union

      public static <E> @Unmodifiable Set<E> union(@NotNull @NotNull @Unmodifiable Set<E> a, @NotNull @NotNull @Unmodifiable Set<E> b)
      Returns a new set containing the elements of 2 given sets The returned set is immutable. The passed sets should be also be immutable. Changes to the underlying sets are not guaranteed to be reflected!
      Type Parameters:
      E - the type of the elements
      Parameters:
      a - the first set
      b - the other set
      Returns:
      a new set containing the elements of the given sets

    • difference
